narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Research is great! Once you've established yourself with a particular lab, it is informative and can be easy to complete a half credit, so you can still be engaged in lab discussion and keep a manageable schedule.

Psyc 495 allowed me to explore different variables, subjects and how to generalize findings to a population, along with how to write IRB's for research subjects. Yes, I would recommend the course to a fellow student because it was an enjoyable way to learn more about research methods of psychology.

PSYC 495 is a great way to get experience in a lab without a large time commitment. Even if you're not a psyc major, it's a good way to get some exposure and see if research is the route that you want to take with your academic career.
